* Getting started
** Dependencies
In a virtual environment:

  - Flask ~python3 -m pip install flask~
  - Flask CORS ~python3 -m pip install flask-cors~
  - Flask Migrate ~python3 -m pip install Flask-Migrate~
  - Psycopg2 ~python3 -m pip install psycopg2-binary~
  - (JWT) Python-Jose ~python3 -m pip install python-jose~
  - Postgres installation -> https://www.postgresql.org/download/

  In one command  ~python3 -m pip install flask flask-cors Flask-Migrate psycopg2-binary python-jose~

** Getting started

*** Set up database
    1. Log in with ~sudo -u postgres -i~
    2. Create the database with ~createdb agency~

*** Migrate the database
    After setting ~FLASK_APP=agency~ run ~flask db init~ then ~flask db migrate~
    and finally ~flask db upgrade~ to apply the migration.

* Casting Agency Specifications
    The Casting Agency models a company that is responsible for
    creating movies and managing and assigning actors to those
    movies. You are an Executive Producer within the company and are
    creating a system to simplify and streamline your process.

** Models [2/2]
   - [X] Movies with attributes title and release date
   - [X] Actors with attributes name, age and gender
** Endpoints [1/8]
 - [X] GET /actors and /movies
 - [ ] GET /actors/<actor_id>/movies
 - [ ] POST /actors
 - [ ] POST /actors/<actor_id>/movies
 - [ ] DELETE /movies/<movie_id>
 - [ ] DELETE /actors/<actor_id>
 - [ ] PATCH /movies/<movie_id>
 - [ ] PATCH /actors/<actor_id>


** Roles [3/3]
 - [X] Casting Assistant
 - [X] Can view actors and movies
 - [X] Casting Director
   - [X] All permissions a Casting Assistant has and…
     - [X] Add or delete an actor from the database
     - [X] Modify actors or movies
   - [X] Executive Producer
     - [X] All permissions a Casting Director has and…
     - [X] Add or delete a movie from the database
** Tests [0/3]
 - [ ] One test for success behavior of each endpoint
 - [ ] One test for error behavior of each endpoint
 - [ ] At least two tests of RBAC for each role
